    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "Just wanted to document where and how Web3.js is used within `@truffle/decoder` (`@truffle/codec` only uses `web3-utils` which is relatively lightweight). The intention is to find out how coupled we are with Web3.js and whether or not it is feasible to decouple from it.\r\n\r\nBased on commit [`98ae40e3ef2ee729f1d5d227dcb0ea92b90db60d`](https://github.com/trufflesuite/truffle/tree/98ae40e3ef2ee729f1d5d227dcb0ea92b90db60d/packages/decoder).\r\n\r\n#### `utils.ts`\r\n\r\n- [Line 141](https://github.com/trufflesuite/truffle/blob/next/packages/decoder/lib/utils.ts#L141): \r\n\r\n  ```js\r\n  Web3.utils.toChecksumAddress(value);\r\n  ```\r\n\r\n#### `index.ts`\r\n\r\n- [Line 156](https://github.com/trufflesuite/truffle/blob/next/packages/decoder/lib/index.ts#L156) the Provider constructor from Web3.js is used:\r\n\r\n  ```js\r\n  import { Provider } from \"web3/providers\";\r\n  ```\r\n\r\n- [Line 231](https://github.com/trufflesuite/truffle/blob/next/packages/decoder/lib/index.ts#L231) the `forContract()` function accepts a variable `contract` where it expects a nested `web3` object to grab the `currentProvider`:\r\n\r\n  ```js\r\n  return await forArtifact(contract, contract.web3.currentProvider, artifacts);\r\n  ```\r\n\r\n#### `types.ts`\r\n\r\n- The structure of the following interfaces are informed by Web3.js object structures:\r\n  - `Log`\r\n  - `DecodedLog`\r\n  - `Transaction `\r\n\r\n- [Line 255](https://github.com/trufflesuite/truffle/blob/next/packages/decoder/lib/types.ts#L255) the `ContractConstructorObject` interface includes a web3 instance inside of it.\r\n\r\n#### `decoders.ts`\r\n\r\n- `web3.eth.getCode(address, block)`\r\n- `web3.eth.getBlock(block))`\r\n- `web3.eth.getPastLogs({ address, fromBlock, toBlock })`\r\n- `web3.eth.net.getId()`\r\n- `web3.utils.isAddress(address)`\r\n- `web3.utils.toChecksumAddress(address)`\r\n- `web3.eth.getBlockNumber()`\r\n- `web3.eth.getBalance(address, blockNum)`\r\n- `web3.eth.getTransactionCount(address, blockNum)`\r\n- `web3.eth.getStorageAt(address, slot, block)`\r\n",
